name: KFC Jalan Mas Puteh

reviews.text: The manager was super helpful and friendly.  Plus, all the staff were so sweet.  They had big smiles and were happy to help with everything.  It really made my experience great.  Definitely coming back to this location!

A cute little KFC outlet located in a shophouse. There were only three tables to sit a maximum of 12 pax inside the air conditioned restaurant. Two more tables of 4 located outside the restaurant. Though small, we always managed to find seats to dine in easily. The taste is expected of all KFC outlets. Tried out some new items on the menu like the mala chicken and ondeh ondeh egg tarts. Both were good and we could accept the taste. But these days, dining at KFC is no longer cheap. Thought the prices have increased substantially. Parking lots right outside the restaurant.

The sauce coats each strand of noodles perfectly.  Zinger chicken adds a savory depth to the comforting dish. This warm and inviting meal is perfect for a cozy evening. The combination of chicken and noodles is truly a classic.
